;SEVCONFIELD DESCRIPTION=Determines how speed limit integral (in torque mode) is initialized when starting to limit. Integral is set equal to actual torque multiplied by this factor. Normally, integral is set equal to actual torque so this object is set to 1.0 (1000h). This object is not used in speed mode.

[4651sub8]
ParameterName=Speed calculation filter pole
ParameterValue=0xeca5
ObjectType=7
DataType=6
AccessType=rw
LowLimit=0
HighLimit=65535
PDOMapping=0
DefaultValue=0xF384
;SEVCONFIELD OBJECT_VERSION=1
;SEVCONFIELD ACCESS_LEVEL=4
;SEVCONFIELD SCALING=1.52587890625E-05
;SEVCONFIELD DESCRIPTION=Used to filter speed used for speed limit and speed control loop. When enabled it will bypass any existing filtering within Gen4 encoder to allow full control of the speed feedback and find a compromise between noise and lag. Setting to zero disables this filter and uses the default in encoder handler (Gen4: 3Hz for sin-cos, 9Hz for UVW). It is calculated P = e^(-0.005*2*pi*fc) where fc is the desired cut-off frequency (Hz). Calculation is P = e^(-0.001*2*pi*fc) for HVLP and D8

